<br>
ToN is looking for possible targets.  We see that Lord Seru is up.  TWC is in Santus Seru, so we don't move.  We'd like to kill him, but it appears that TWC is there for him already.  So we keep looking for targets.<br>
<br>
About 30 - 45 minutes later, ToN finds out TWC isn't moving towards Lord Seru, but instead they are apparently killing the house heads/guild masters.  ToN is bored, and looking for something to do kill, so we decide to make Lord Seru our target  If they were in the Lord Seru building, we would leave - if they weren't, we'd move forward.  We group up, go anon like we've done for every relatively big encounter lately, and begin porting into Seru's building.<br>
<br>
I get there with the first group of ToN and see no one else besides our group in the arx.  I do a /who &quot;The War Council&quot; (this will show people even if they're anon) and see about 24 people.  Do it again a few minutes later, and see 14... again 13.. again 25.  It's bouncing all over the place so I wasnt sure exactly what was happening.  Maybe they're wiping.. maybe they killed the house masters and decided to leave.  From what some of the few people I know in TWC have told me, they usually start their raiding VERY late night so maybe they did call it a night - but I really don't know what is going on with them.  I wouldn't expect TWC to wipe to a house master, but stranger things have happened in this game.<br>
<br>
We get about 3 groups into Lord Seru's building then TWC begins to show up in Seru's building.  One or two of their guys port in naked so it's my guess they knew we were there and had cleared a few of the guards there, because although it's not a difficult fight upon port in, it's not the brightest thing to go into it with no gear on.  So it would be my guess that TWC made Lord Seru their target upon noticing ToN port in, or changed their plans upon seeing us move on Lord Seru and moved their raid time up so they wouldn't lose him to us.<br>
<br>
Next, a GM pops into Lord Seru's building.  Apparently a TWC member had a petition in for some lost gear and the GM was returning it to him - this is key point in the afternoon unfortunately.<br>
<br>
TWC had more porters available than ToN so they get 3 or 4 groups ported up fairly quickly.  But since (again, it's my guess since I can't read their minds) they weren't prepared for Seru, they were rushing to get people so after the first 3 or 4 groups or so they ported in, the rate at which they were moving in slowed down considerably.<br>
<br>
/who's show we build up at about 25 to about 25, .. to about 36 to 36.. to ultimately at about 42 to about 42.  If they were in the building, or just in the zone I'm not positive on, but never do their numbers go above our numbers or our numbers go above them after the first set of groups have ported in.  Very even numbers the entire time.<br>
<br>
When ToN finishes porting up we start to move/clear to Lord Seru.  TWC does not move, but 2 TWC members (Nandarie is one, I think her cleric was another) follow us up the entire way, so they know where we are every step of the way.<br>
<br>
ToN moves up to just before the Lord Seru area, but we had a cleric AFK upon porting in and get left behind (when you gotta go, you gotta go I guess) so we get hung up for a couple minutes while we get the person back to the raid. (I believe he ended up dying and TWC actually rezzed him, which was very nice of one of their clerics).<br>
<br>
We move up to the final room start killing the stationary guards and roaming guards.  After we've killed a lot of the roamers and the nearby stationary guards, TWC clicks up into the final hallway, and quickly moves down the hallway while we're killing some of the mobs we just pulled.  They kill few of the guards inside his room and sits their entire raid inside the Lord Seru room into the spot we were preparing to set up.<br>
<br>
So we're in a bit of a bind and can't move in unless we want to double up on top of each other.<br>
<br>
At this point a GM comes.  The GM remembers seeing the TWC player in the Lord Seru building port in earlier because he answered a petition there for one of their members.  He didn't necessarily remember ToN there because frankly he didn't look.  He also sees TWC inside the Seru room, and not us - again not seeing that TWC moved past us at the last moment.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, because the GM had only 2 data points to base his information from, he sided with TWC.  From those two slices of time,  it appeared that TWC was ahead of us the entire time.  So we are told to leave the zone because he wants no claims/complaints of training.<br>
<br>
I'm not happy with what happened the other night, but to dwell on it would be pointless.<br>
<br>
I'm not going to say we were right and they were wrong and I'm not going to say they were right and we were wrong.  Whether something is &quot;Right&quot; or &quot;Wrong&quot; when behavior is concerned is up to the person and how they were raised.  Some people cheat on their wife, and don't see that as wrong - others do see it as wrong.  Some people have 2 wives, and don't see that as wrong - others do.  It's all a matter of opinions and value sets.<br>
<br>
To get into a pissing match whether something is right or wrong is a never ending argument, so I won't go there.  Some things are just based on opinion and opinion only - actions and behavior is one of them.<br>
<br>
My personal view is, TWC was not in the Lord Seru building.  They were killing house masters.  Lord Seru was not being moved on so we made him our target.  Similar to ToV for example.  If Guild A is killing Telkenor, and Guild B decides to make LTK their target and moves to them, In my opinion it would be silly of Guild A to say they were FIF for LTK because they were in the zone.  Granted some zones require clearing before the &quot;boss&quot; can be engaged, Plane of Fear and Plane of Growth for example - but Sanctus Seru is not such a zone.  Some mobs need to be spawned/triggered.. again, Lord Seru is not such a mob.<br>
<br>
If you're bored and have nothing better to do, fine continue to argue about this.  But in my eyes it's a dead issue - what's done is done.  TWC did nothing to surprise me last night.  I don't think we did anything out of the ordinary for us either.  Just a clash in styles and beliefs.<br>
<br>
Numnayan asked what was up with TWC running over ToN, that's what happened in my eyes.<br>
<br>
Anyways, The Saryrn Tavern Blast furnace isn't where I like to spend my time generally because of the amount of BS that flys around here so don't expect me to post again here on this topic.. if you really want to say something to me, send me a tell in game.  The Blast Furnace as a form of entertainment doesn't really work for me so most of the times I don't read it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71154" target="top">Shagz</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
